---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = '/penzana-del-merel';
const events = [
  { year: '1936', label: 'Acquisition' },
  { year: '1959', label: 'Inn opens' },
  { year: '1989', label: 'Naples finalist' },
  { year: '1990s', label: 'Pizzeria begins' },
  { year: 'Today', label: 'Third generation' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Our story — La Penzana del Merel"
  description="The story of La Penzana del Merel: from the original building and inn to the family pizzeria of today. Bergamo roots, three generations, one hillside memory."
  lang="en"
  currentPath={`${base}/en/history/`}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container page-hero__inner">
      <span class="page-hero__eyebrow">History</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">A story of ovens, hillside air and a family that stayed.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__lead">From the original building to the inn, from Trattoria Cima Verde to today's pizzeria: one continuous line shaped by place, ritual and people.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="display:grid; gap:1.2rem; max-width:960px;">
      <div class="timeline-pills reveal">
        {events.map((ev) => (
          <div class="timeline-pill">
            <span class="timeline-pill__label">{ev.label}</span>
            <span class="timeline-pill__year">{ev.year}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="page-content-shell reveal">
        <h2>1936 — The building</h2>
        <figure class="editorial-figure" style="margin:1rem 0 1.25rem;">
          <img src={`${base}/img/trattoria_alpina_historical_photo.png`} alt="Historic photo of the original building in Orezzo" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Orezzo — Trattoria Alpina, the original building.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>The building is acquired in 1936 by Alessandro Merelli. For a few decades it is rented out, but it remains a recognisable landmark in the village of Orezzo.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-content-shell reveal">
        <h2>31 December 1959 — The inn opens</h2>
        <p>Tarcisio, Alessandro's son, opens the inn under the name Trattoria Cima Verde. It becomes a place of summer afternoons, glasses of red wine at the counter, bowls and the shade of the century-old chestnut tree.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote">Glasses of red at the counter, bowls under the old chestnut tree. A place where time still had permission to slow down.</blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="page-content-shell reveal">
        <h2>1989 — Passion for the oven</h2>
        <p>Tarcisio develops a passion for building food ovens. In 1989 he becomes a finalist at the Naples Centenary of the Margherita pizza, a rare recognition for a craftsman from Bergamo.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-content-shell reveal">
        <h2>1990s — La Penzana del Merel</h2>
        <p>With the help of his son Efrem and daughter-in-law Laura Merla, the inn becomes a pizzeria. The name recalls the simple tin-roofed shelters where farmers stored rakes and pitchforks — an image rooted in local land and labour.</p>
        <p>From the first years, the pizzas and the setting attract people looking for cool summer evenings, hillside dinners and a genuinely local place.</p>
        <figure class="editorial-figure" style="margin:1rem 0 1.25rem;">
          <img src={`${base}/img/general_pizza_overview.png`} alt="Fresh pizzas from the wood-fired oven" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Pizzas at La Penzana — crafted with care in every detail.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="story-quote reveal">
        <p>"We want to change in order to remain ourselves, and remain with you."</p>
        <span class="story-quote__cite">The Merel family</span>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-row reveal">
        <a href={`${base}/en/family/`} class="btn btn-primary">The family today</a>
        <a href={`${base}/en/menu/`} class="btn btn-outline">See the menu</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
